name: MajorSurgicalProcedure
title: Major Surgical Procedure
description: The intent of this value set is to identify an exclusionary population of patients who had a major surgery from a measure focused on a medication-related adverse major bleeding event.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Major surgery defined as a procedure associated with expected blood loss of >500 mL, significant fluid shifts, and typically at least one night in the hospital.  Includes laparoscopic surgery with a few exceptions, open resection of organs, large joint replacements, mastectomy with immediate reconstruction, spine, thoracic, vascular, and intracranial surgery.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have had  a selected major surgery.   Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Procedure category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include ICD 10 PCS codes that identify selected major surgeries.),(Exclusion Criteria: Laparoscopic cholecystectomy, tubal ligation, and surgeries deemed 'minor' by not meeting the criteria for inclusion.)
